{"id":"1701.07385","submitter":"Zhouyang Ge","authors":"Zhouyang Ge, Jean-Christophe Loiseau, Outi Tammisola, Luca Brandt","title":"An efficient mass-preserving interface-correction level set/ghost fluid\n  method for droplet suspensions under depletion forces","comments":null,"journal-ref":"J. Comp. Phys., Volume 353, 15 January 2018, Pages 435-459","doi":"10.1016/j.jcp.2017.10.046","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.flu-dyn","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Aiming for the simulation of colloidal droplets in microfluidic devices, we\npresent here a numerical method for two-fluid systems subject to surface\ntension and depletion forces among the suspended droplets. The algorithm is\nbased on an efficient solver for the incompressible two-phase Navier-Stokes\nequations, and uses a mass-conserving level set method to capture the fluid\ninterface. The four novel ingredients proposed here are, firstly, an\ninterface-correction level set (ICLS) method; global mass conservation is\nachieved by performing an additional advection near the interface, with a\ncorrection velocity obtained by locally solving an algebraic equation, which is\neasy to implement in both 2D and 3D. Secondly, we report a second-order\naccurate geometric estimation of the curvature at the interface and, thirdly,\nthe combination of the ghost fluid method with the fast pressure-correction\napproach enabling an accurate and fast computation even for large density\ncontrasts. Finally, we derive a hydrodynamic model for the interaction forces\ninduced by depletion of surfactant micelles and combine it with a multiple\nlevel set approach to study short-range interactions among droplets in the\npresence of attracting forces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Jan 2017 17:20:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2017 09:36:15 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 24 Oct 2017 17:08:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-15"}
